<br>
Though you gotta wonder why debate about this after all that has happened.  In the past few months since Ragefire has been moved to Skyfire, larger guilds actually now have a harder time getting Rage than before (not many guilds can keep the fire giants cleared at all times, now they don't have to) ... smaller guilds are ganging up against the 'higher end' guilds in alliances, and like it was said before larger guilds tend to be raiding elsewhere rather than keeping an eye out on Ragefire all the time.<br>
<br>
I would say the ratio of Ragefires, between higher end/lower end guilds are about 1:4.  <br>
<br>
What am I trying to prove?  I'm trying to prove that despite the 'racing' method that has been implemented by the minority of 'higher end' guilds the lower end ones ended up on top, anyways.  No high end guild is actively camping Ragefire anymore because they're now all beyond doing epics on a consistent basis, so really it's all about gaining a little bit of edge in what otherwise is a monopolized spawn by all the smaller guilds (since the smaller guilds don't have to raid other stuff everyday).<br>
<br>
Really, think about it ... which people got Ragefire in the last few spawns and how many of them belong to Harmonium/AV/SM/OC/Concordance/TH?<br>
<br>
By the way, kiting Ragefire and waiting for your forces to show up is not an acceptable method of engagement. <p><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="400">
